Function DEFER-INTERRUPT, REJECT-INTERRUPT

Syntax:

  defer-interrupt interrupt =>|
  reject-interrupt interrupt =>|

Arguments and Values:

  interrupt - an interrupt.

Description:

  Transfers control to the most recently established applicable restart having
  the same name as the function. That is, the function DEFER-INTERRUPT searches
  for an applicable DEFER-INTERRUPT restart, and the function REJECT-INTERRUPT
  searches for an applicable REJECT-INTERRUPT restart.

  If interrupt is not an interrupt currently being signaled, an error of type
  CONTROL-ERROR is signaled.
